author: Elastic
attributes.description: Identifies suspicious instances of default system32 DLLs either unsigned or signed with non-MS certificates. This can potentially indicate the attempt to masquerade as system DLLs, perform DLL Search Order Hijacking or backdoor and resign legitimate DLLs.
attributes.name: Potential Masquerading as System32 DLL
attributes.query:
library where event.action == "load" and
    not (
      dll.path : (
        "?:\\Windows\\System32\\*",
        "?:\\Windows\\SysWOW64\\*",
        "?:\\Windows\\SystemTemp\\*",
        "?:\\$WINDOWS.~BT\\NewOS\\Windows\\WinSxS\\*",
        "?:\\$WINDOWS.~BT\\NewOS\\Windows\\System32\\*",
        "?:\\Windows\\WinSxS\\*",
        "?:\\Windows\\SoftwareDistribution\\Download\\*",
        "?:\\Windows\\assembly\\NativeImages_v*"
      )
    ) and
    not (
      dll.code_signature.subject_name in (
        "Microsoft Windows",
        "Microsoft Corporation",
        "Microsoft Windows Hardware Abstraction Layer Publisher",
        "Microsoft Windows Publisher",
        "Microsoft Windows 3rd party Component",
        "Microsoft 3rd Party Application Component"
      ) and dll.code_signature.trusted == true
